  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Prospective, blinded, placebo-controlled trial. Patients: Adult patients (&gt;18 years of age)
      undergoing de novo Htx, with a preoperative GFR &gt; 30ml/min, not receiving an ABO-incompatible
      organ with an ischemia time of &gt; 6 hours. A donor age &gt; 70 years is an exclusion criteria.

      Intervention: Infusion of h-ANP fore five days, starting at the induction of anesthesia.

      Outcome: Kidney function, evaluated with serum creatinine day 1-7 and kidney clearance, 4-5
      Days after Htx plus after 3 and 12 months.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
